.TH SSO 1 "MARCH 2024" "1.0" "Bandit SSO Manual"
.SH NAME
sso \- Streamlined SSH utility for OverTheWire Bandit wargame
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sso
[\fI-p level\fR] [\fI-l\fR] [\fI-h\fR] [\fIpassword|keyfile\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sso
automates credential management and connections for Bandit levels. 
It saves passwords to ~/etc/otw/passwds.txt and manages SSH keys in ~/etc/otw/keys/.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B sso
Connect to the highest reached level.
.TP
.B sso <password|keyfile>
Test credentials for the next level; if successful, saves them.
.TP
.B sso -p <level>
Connect to a specific level using saved credentials.
.TP
.B sso -p <level> <pass>
Connect to a specific level and update it with a new password.
.TP
.B sso -l
List all saved credentials in a table format.
.TP
.B sso -h
Show the help menu.
.SH FILES
.I ~/etc/otw/passwds.txt
Stored passwords for Bandit levels.
.I ~/etc/otw/keys/
Stored SSH private keys.

